\begin_layout Subsection
Financial Statements Analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The FSA is important, as financial statements are very complex and hardly
 comparable across firms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is a 5 step process: 
\series bold
identifying
\series default
 economic charasteristics of the industry, 
\series bold
assessing
\series default
 financial statement, 
\series bold
analyzing
\series default
, preparing 
\series bold
forecast
\series default
 and 
\series bold
valuing
\series default
 the firm.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The goal is using accounting data in order to analyze risk and profitability
 of a company.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The tools in use for the analysis are common-size financial statements,
 percentage change statements and financial statements ratios.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Common-Size Statements
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Common-size financial statement means using 
\series bold
percentage ratios
\series default
 and not absolute values (in ths B/S or the I/S).
 It allows comparison across different firms in the industry
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Consider an example with a B/S where the revenue increases, but the net
 income 
\series bold
percentage
\series default
 (of the revenue) decreases.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Profitability Ratios
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Profitability ratios are designed to measure earnings power of a firm.
 They are calculated by comparing the net income to other financial activity
 of a firm, in order to assess its performance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Return on equity (ROE)
\series default
 is net income, divided by the average shareholders' equity.
 It provides a measure of the 
\series bold
effectiveness
\series default
 of capital management.
 The net income is a periodic number, which comes from the I/S.
 The SSE comes from the B/S which is a point in time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The problem is dividing a periodic number by a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

point in time
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 figure.
 It is solved by measuring the average SSE (using 2 periodic numbers).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Company's value is impacted mainly by the operating activity.
\end_layout

