B/S Reformulation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The ROE can be divided to operating return and non-operating return.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Reformulating the B/S is rewriting it in a functional way (operating vs.
 financing): net operating assets = net financial obligations + common sharehold
ers' equity (
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

moving
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 some parts to the other part of the equation).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The moment we have identified financial assets & liabilities - everything
 else is 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

operating
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Financial liabilities minus financial assets give the 
\series bold
net financial obligation
